      "full_body_preview": "There was a clockmaker in a town that did not use clocks.\n\nShe had inherited the shop from her father, who had inherited it from his, and so on back to a great-grandfather who had built the first clock in the region. By her time the townspeople had decided clocks were impolite — they made appointments hard, made waiting feel like loss, made dying feel scheduled. So they put the clocks in cupboards and lived by the bells of the temple and the sun on the hills.\n\nThe clockmaker kept the shop open. "
